headline: Trump likely to roll back but not dismantle Biden's clean energy spending
summary: President-elect Trump has previously slammed Biden's signature Inflation Reduction Act. But pressure from GOP lawmakers, whose districts have benefited from clean energy investments, suggests the law is more likely to be stripped down than repealed.
